    <p>PARIS • Kenyan Daniel Wan­jiru, the 2017 London Marathon win­ner, has been banned for four years due to an ath­lete bi­o­log­i­cal pass­port vi­o­la­tion, the sport’s in­de­pen­dent Ath­let­ics In­tegrity Unit said.</p>
    <p>Wan­jiru, who has de­nied any wrong­do­ing, was pro­vi­sion­ally sus­pended in April and his ban has been back­dated to Dec 9 last year.</p>


